post_text: The Sartell-St. Stephen ISD 748 School Board approved an In-Person Learning Model for PreK-Grade 5 & a Hybrid Learning Model for Grades 6-12 to start the 2020-21 school year at their 8/17 meeting. As required by the MN Department of Health (MDH), the decision was based on known Stearns County COVID-19 case rates through 8/1. Data regarding Stearns County cases is released to the school district every Thursday w/ updated case rates, so there is potential that infection levels will decrease enough to allow ALL PreK-12 students to return to school in an In-Person Learning Model. **The final decision regarding the September 8 Learning Model will be made & communicated to families on 8/27.** https://www.sartell.k12.mn.us/backtoschool2020

post_text: It was Global Play Day at Pine Meadow Elementary today. February 4, 2015, was the first annual Global School Play Day for students in schools around the world. The purpose of Global School Play Day is to educate others on the benefits and the necessity of unstructured play. No devices are allowed. Students played group games such as 7-Up, board games, legos and with favorite toys. They built forts with blankets, put together puzzles and played outside. They painted and drew their favorites pictures and created many works of art. It was a great day of learning and play!

post_text: While we think every week should be a Recognition Week for staff, Gov. Tim Walz has officially proclaimed January 27-31 Paraprofessional Recognition Week! There are over 20,000 paraprofessionals in MN working hard every day to make sure every child has the education they need to succeed in school and life. Their roles include special education paraprofessionals, student support assistants and health office assistants. THANK YOU ISD 748 paraprofessionals!
